D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuk-accidentally-sent-classified-information-mali-russian-allied-country-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690516378000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c3239d048ff200190c66de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuk-accidentally-sent-classified-information-mali-russian-allied-country-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20UK%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20has%20launched%20an%20investigation%20into%20the%20matter.%20Millions%20of%20US%20military%20emails%20were%20sent%20to%20Mali%20due%20to%20the%20same%20error.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktan%40insider.com%20(Kwan%20Wei%20Kevin%20Tan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuk-accidentally-sent-classified-information-mali-russian-allied-country-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Eight%20Months%20Later%2C%20India%20Says%20Modi%2C%20Xi%20Did%20Talk%20About%20Stabilising%20Ties%20at%20Bali%20Encounter%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28091355%2Fmodi-xi-bishek-pib.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Ahead%20of%20likely%20meetings%20between%20the%20two%20leaders%20at%20the%20G20%20and%20BRICS%20summits%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20on%20Thursday%20said%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20had%20exchanged%20courtesies%20with%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20and%20spoken%20about%20the%20need%20to%20%E2%80%9Cstabilise%E2%80%9D%20bilateral%20relations%20at%20an%20encounter%20during%20last%20November%E2%80%99s%20G20%20summit%20dinner%20in%20Bali.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20on%20Monday%2C%20the%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20had%20claimed%20that%20Xi%20and%20Modi%20had%20reached%20an%20%E2%80%9Cimportant%20consensus%20stabilising%20China-India%20relations%20in%20Bali%E2%80%9D.%20This%20was%20part%20of%20the%20press%20release%20issued%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fwang-yi-ajit-doval-india-china-brics%5C%22%3Emeeting%20between%20China%E2%80%99s%20top%20diplomat%20Wang%20Yi%20and%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Ajit%20Doval%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20BRICS%20summit%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20July%2024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20weekly%20press%20briefing%2C%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20spokesperson%20Arindam%20Bagchi%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CNow%20if%20you%20would%20recall%20that%20during%20the%20Bali%20G20%20Summit%20last%20year%2C%20we%20had%20said%2C%20foreign%20secretary%20had%20said%20at%20briefing%2C%20that%20prime%20minister%20and%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20at%20the%20conclusion%20of%20that%20dinner%20hosted%20by%20the%20Indonesian%20President%2C%20they%20exchanged%20courtesies%20and%20also%20spoke%20of%20the%20need%20to%20stabilise%20our%20bilateral%20relations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20pointed%20out%20that%20foreign%20secretary%20Vinay%20Kwatra%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fg20-modi-biden-xi-jinping%5C%22%3Eonly%20said%20that%20the%20leaders%20had%20exchanged%20courtesies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Bagchi%20clarified%20that%20the%20second%20part%20of%20the%20reply%20was%20%E2%80%9Cmy%20statement%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20think%20foreign%20secretary%20did%20mention%2C%20maybe%20he%20did%20not%20mention%20the%20second%20part%20of%20it.%20He%20did%20talk%20about%20exchanging%20courtesies%20and%20I%20think%20there%20was%20the%20general%20discussion%20or%20spoke%20of%20the%20need%20to%20stabilise%20our%20bilateral%20relationship%20or%20relations%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20he%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20India%E2%80%99s%20view%20on%20%E2%80%9Cstabilising%E2%80%9D%20the%20relations%2C%20the%20MEA%20spokesperson%20reiterated%20that%20India%20has%20%E2%80%9Csteadfastly%20maintained%20that%20the%20key%20to%20resolution%20of%20this%20whole%20issue%20is%20to%20resolve%20the%20situation%20along%20the%20LAC%20on%20the%20western%20sector%20of%20the%20India-China%20boundary%20and%20to%20restore%20peace%20and%20tranquility%20in%20the%20border%20areas%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20acknowledgment%20of%20the%20Chinese%20version%20of%20the%20Bali%20encounter%20is%20likely%20related%20to%20creating%20a%20conducive%20atmosphere%20as%20the%20Indian%20establishment%20gets%20ready%20for%20the%20Chinese%20president%20to%20come%20to%20New%20Delhi%20for%20the%20G20%20summit%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20reply%20to%20another%20question%2C%20the%20MEA%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CG20%20is%20not%20too%20far%20away%20and%20we%20are%20making%20all%20efforts%20and%20preparations%20to%20ensure%20that%20it%20is%20a%20success%20with%20participation%20of%20all%20the%20leaders%20invited.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20host%2C%20Modi%20will%20certainly%20have%20a%20bilateral%20meeting%20with%20his%20Chinese%20guest.%20Similarly%2C%20if%20Modi%20travels%20for%20the%20BRICS%20meeting%20in%20Johannesburg%2C%20it%20would%20have%20also%20mean%20another%20meeting%20among%20the%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20still%20not%20clear%20why%20the%20two%20sides%20did%20not%20mention%20that%20there%20was%20talk%20about%20stabilising%20relations%20at%20the%20G20%20dinner%20in%20Indonesia%2C%20which%20was%20the%20first%20time%20that%20Modi%20and%20Xi%20were%20seen%20together%20in%20a%20public%20setting%20since%20the%20two%20militaries%20began%20a%20stand-off%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh%20in%20May%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Indian%20foreign%20secretary%20had%20said%20that%20there%20was%20an%20exchange%20of%20pleasantries%2C%20the%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fmprc.gov.cn%2Feng%2Ftopics_665678%2F2022%2Fcxesgjtytjhtg%2F%5C%22%3Enot%20even%20publicly%20recorded%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20encounter%20in%20Xi%E2%80%99s%20engagements%20at%20the%20G20%20summit%20in%20Indonesia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20November%202022%20G20%20summit%2C%20there%20had%20been%20no%20visible%20thaw%20in%20India-China%20relations.%20Despite%20the%20multiple%20rounds%20of%20diplomatic%20and%20military%20talks%20since%20then%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20change%20in%20the%20postures%20of%20the%20two%20countries%20on%20the%20border%20situation.%20While%20India%20insists%20that%20the%20stand-off%20will%20end%20only%20after%20there%20is%20resolution%20of%20Demchok%20and%20Depsang%2C%20China%20claims%20that%20these%20two%20areas%20are%20not%20part%20of%20the%20change%20in%20status%20quo%20after%20May%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20also%20refused%20to%20extend%20the%20visas%20of%20Chinese%20journalists%20based%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20which%20has%20meant%20that%20there%20is%20currently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fno-more-chinese-journalists-in-india-visa-renewal-denied-for-the-lone-reporter%5C%22%3Eno%20representative%20from%20a%20Chinese%20media%20outlet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20a%20tit-for-tat%2C%20China%20also%20brought%20down%20the%20number%20of%20Indian%20journalists%20to%20just%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20China%20had%20also%20put%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fchina-again-puts-technical-hold-on-unsc-sanctioning-jems-rauf-azhar%5C%22%3Ehold%20on%20the%20proposal%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20listing%20of%20Jaish-e-Mohammed%20(JeM)%20terrorist%20Abdul%20Rauf%20Azhar%20on%20the%20sanctions%20list%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council.%20A%20month%20later%2C%20China%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fchina-blocks-unsc-listing-of-lets-sajid-mir-as-a-global-terrorist%5C%22%3Eagain%20blocked%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20proposal%20to%20designate%20Lashkar-e-Taiba%20(LeT)%20terrorist%20and%2026%2F11%20mastermind%20Sajid%20Mir%20as%20a%20global%20terrorist%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20hosting%20several%20rounds%20of%20meetings%20at%20various%20levels%20as%20chair%2C%20India%20surprisingly%20turned%20the%20Shanghai%20Cooperation%20Organisation%20summit%20into%20a%20video%20conference.%20This%20had%20led%20to%20speculation%20that%20Modi%20was%20not%20too%20eager%20to%20be%20seen%20with%20the%20Pakistan%20and%20Chinese%20premiers%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%202024%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20repeated%20questions%20about%20Chinese%20incursion%20into%20the%20Indian%20side%20of%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%2C%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20said%20the%20situation%20at%20the%20border%20was%20not%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Cland%20grab%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fon-china-jaishankar-says-dispute-is-over-forward-deployment-not-about-land-grab%5C%22%3Eforward%20deployment%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20of%20Chinese%20troops%20at%20the%20LAC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20another%20event%20on%20June%2028%2C%20Jaishankar%20asserted%20that%20the%20border%20situation%20between%20India%20and%20China%20remained%20%E2%80%9Cabnormal%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20immediately%20impacted%20bilateral%20ties.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20bottom%20line%20there%20is%20that%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20the%20state%20of%20the%20border%20will%20determine%20the%20state%20of%20the%20relationship%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fstate-of-border-still-abnormal-s-jaishankar-on-ties-with-china-4161512%5C%22%3Estate%20of%20the%20border%20today%20is%20still%20abnormal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%20Jaishankar%20had%20met%20with%20Wang%20Yi%20during%20the%20BRICS%20foreign%20ministers%E2%80%99%20meeting%2C%20but%20the%20Chinese%20reference%20had%20not%20made%20any%20reference%20to%20Bali.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20India%20moving%20largely%20in%20sync%20with%20the%20US%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20there%20is%20also%20a%20growing%20gap%20with%20China%20on%20the%20strategic%20front%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ffor-the-first-time-india-calls-for-abiding-by-the-2016-arbitral-award-on-south-china-sea%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20reported%20that%20India%20had%20changed%20its%20position%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20last%20seven%20years%20and%20for%20the%20first%20time%20explicitly%20called%20for%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%202016%20arbitration%20ruling%20that%20had%20struck%20down%20China%E2%80%99s%20territorial%20claims%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20China%20issued%20stapled%20visas%20to%20Wushu%20sportspersons%20from%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%20which%20India%20described%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunacceptable%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStating%20that%20India%20was%20aware%20of%20the%20developments%2C%20Bagchi%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20unacceptable%20and%20we%20have%20lodged%20our%20strong%20protest%20with%20the%20Chinese%20side%20reiterating%20our%20consistent%20position%20on%20the%20matter%20and%20India%20reserves%20the%20right%20to%20suitably%20respond%20to%20such%20actions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20stated%20that%20India%20has%20repeatedly%20maintained%20that%20there%20%E2%80%9Cshould%20be%20no%20discrimination%20or%20differential%20treatment%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20domicile%20or%20ethnicity%20in%20the%20visa%20regime%20for%20Indian%20citizens%20holding%20valid%20Indian%20passports%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20boundary%20dispute%2C%20China%20claims%20the%20whole%20of%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20as%20%E2%80%98South%20Tibet%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20is%20not%20recognised%20by%20India.%20The%20issuance%20of%20stapled%20visas%20for%20residents%20of%20Arunachal%20has%20been%20a%20long-standing%20practice%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.g