6331766.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Trinity%20Site%20From%20%E2%80%98Oppenheimer%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20Reminder%20of%20the%20Horror%20of%20Nuclear%20Weapons%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27163230%2FVisits-at-Trinity-Site.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F20%2Fmovies%2Fchristopher-nolan-oppenheimer.html%5C%22%3EChristopher%20Nolan%E2%80%99s%202023%20film%20%3Cem%3EOppenheimer%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20biopic%20about%20the%20theoretical%20physicist%20behind%20the%20atomic%20bomb.%20After%20watching%20the%20film%2C%20I%20was%20inspired%20to%20write%20about%20my%20visit%20to%20the%20actual%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nps.gov%2Fwhsa%2Flearn%2Fhistoryculture%2Ftrinity-site.htm%5C%22%3ETrinity%20site%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20the%20first%20atomic%20bomb%20was%20detonated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20my%20research%20on%20nuclear%20weapons%20and%20civil%20defence%2C%20I%20visited%20the%20Trinity%20site%20in%202015.%20Located%20in%20the%20desert%20in%20the%20southwest%20United%20States%2C%20the%20Trinity%20site%20is%20isolated%2C%20peculiar%20and%20disconcertingly%20mundane.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tower%20that%20held%20the%20bomb%20is%20featured%20prominently%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EOppenheimer%3C%2Fem%3E%20film.%20A%20small%20fragment%20of%20it%20exists%20today%2C%20as%20the%20rest%20of%20it%20was%20vaporised.%20It%20was%20deeply%20unnerving%20being%20near%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%20vaporised%20tower.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F5ZYD-H4V2M0%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArriving%20at%20the%20site%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Trinity%20site%20is%20open%20to%20the%20public%20for%20only%20a%20few%20hours%20twice%20a%20year%2C%20by%20permission%20of%20the%20U.S.%20Army.%20The%20predicted%20popularity%20of%20%3Cem%3EOppenheimer%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0release%20will%20possibly%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhome.army.mil%2Fwsmr%2Findex.php%2Fcontact%2Fpublic-affairs-office%2Ftrinity-site-open-house%5C%22%3Eovercrowd%20the%20next%20open%20house%20on%20Oct.%2021%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20visited%20the%20site%2C%20I%20first%20had%20to%20make%20my%20way%20to%20a%20very%20remote%20area%20of%20the%20New%20Mexico%20desert.%20Arrival%20had%20to%20be%20well%20before%20sunrise%20to%20have%20any%20chance%20of%20being%20in%20the%20small%20group%20of%20persons%20granted%20entry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20after%20waiting%20for%20hours%20at%20the%20secluded%20gate%20of%20an%20active%20missile%20and%20munitions%20testing%20range%2C%20I%20had%20to%20pass%20the%20rigour%20of%20a%20screening%20at%20an%20army%20checkpoint%20and%20closely%20adhere%20to%20a%20given%20set%20of%20rules%20and%20regulations%20verbatim.%20Our%20convoy%2C%20escorted%20by%20military%20police%2C%20then%20went%20to%20a%20more%20remote%20interior%20location%20of%20the%20missile%20testing%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20stopped%20at%20a%20barren%20plain%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fahf.nuclearmuseum.org%2Franger%2Ftour-stop%2Fearly-trinity-site-history%2F%5C%22%3EJornada%20del%20Muerto%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cdead%20man%E2%80%99s%20journey%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20desert.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20then%20walked%20a%20half%20kilometre%20along%20a%20dirt%20path%20leading%20to%20the%20crater.%20A%20chain-link%20fence%20distinguishes%20the%20area%20surrounding%20the%20crater%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20desert.%20The%20blast%20crater%20is%20flatter%20than%20it%20is%20concave.%20The%20fence%20is%20demarcated%20with%20black%20and%20yellow%20signs%20reading%20%E2%80%9CCaution%20Radioactive%20Materials.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVisiting%20the%20site%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20attraction%20at%20the%20Trinity%20site%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Focw.mit.edu%2Fcourses%2F17-473-the-politics-of-nuclear-proliferation-nuclear-history-strategy-and-statecraft-fall-2015%2Fresources%2F17-473f15-th%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20simple%20obelisk%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0made%20of%20volcanic%20rocks%20marking%20Ground%20Zero.%20It%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atomicarchive.com%2Fhistory%2Ftrinity%2Flandmark.html%5C%22%3Eerected%20in%201965%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdjacent%20to%20the%20obelisk%2C%20small%20fragments%20of%20the%20tower%20remained.%20In%20the%20distance%2C%20a%20low%20white%20structure%20shielded%20portions%20of%20the%20crater.%20Green%20glassy%20radioactive%20rocks%2C%20known%20as%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Forau.org%2Fhealth-physics-museum%2Fcollection%2Fnuclear-weapons%2Ftrinity%2Ftrinitite.html%5C%22%3ETrinitite%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0litter%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20very%20few%20elements%20of%20interpretive%20information%20like%20what%20one%20would%20see%20at%20a%20museum.%20Military%20personnel%20dragged%20out%20a%20replica%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.osti.gov%2Fopennet%2Fmanhattan-project-history%2FEvents%2F1945%2Fnagasaki.htm%5C%22%3EFat%20Man%20bomb%20dropped%20on%20Nagasaki%20in%201945%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20served%20to%20occupy%20the%20attention%20of%20most%20visitors%2C%20who%20perhaps%20anticipated%20more%20to%20see%20and%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVaporised%20tower%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20significant%20observation%20I%20made%20at%20the%20Trinity%20site%20was%20a%20small%20fragment%20of%20metal%20in%20the%20ground.%20It%20was%20a%20fragment%20of%20the%20tower%2C%20and%20proof%20of%20physicist%20Albert%20Einstein%E2%80%99s%20theory%20that%20mass%20is%20just%20a%20concentrated%20form%20of%20energy.%20And%20mass%20can%20turn%20to%20energy%20under%20the%20conditions%20of%20an%20atom%20bomb%20detonation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEinstein%E2%80%99s%20famous%20equation%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fscience%2F2014%2Fapr%2F05%2Feinstein-equation-emc2-special-relativity-alok-jha%5C%22%3EE%20%3D%20mc%C2%B2%20explains%20the%20energy%20released%20in%20an%20atomic%20bomb%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20did%20not%20explain%20how%20to%20build%20one.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vanityfair.com%2Fhollywood%2F2023%2F07%2Foppenheimer-einstein-movie-real-life%5C%22%3EEinstein%20and%20Oppenheimer%20were%20colleagues%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20task%20of%20developing%20the%20atomic%20bomb%20was%20designated%20to%20Oppenheimer%20and%20his%20crew.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Trinity%20test%20demonstrated%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnh.org%2Fexhibitions%2Feinstein%2Fenergy%2Fthe-sun-and-the-atom-bomb%5C%22%3Ehumankind%20could%20tap%20the%20essence%20of%20the%20sun%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20bomb%20worked%2C%20creating%20temperatures%20hotter%20than%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2F17137-how-hot-is-the-sun.html%5C%22%3Esun%E2%80%99s%2015%20million%20degrees%20Celsius%20core%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Hot%20gas%20radiated%20its%20energy%20in%20the%20form%20of%20x-rays%2C%20which%20heated%20the%20surrounding%20air%2C%20annihilating%20everything%20in%20their%20path.%20The%20phenomenon%20created%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstr.llnl.gov%2F2018-06%2Frose%5C%22%3Enuclear%20fireball%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tower%20that%20held%20the%20bomb%20last%20existed%20at%205%3A28%20a.m.%20on%20July%2016%2C%201945.%20It%20was%20no%20longer%20in%20existence%20at%205%3A29%20a.m.%2C%20at%20the%20time%20the%20Trinity%20test%20commenced.%20The%20test%20vaporised%20the%20experimental%20structure%2C%20leaving%20behind%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.2101350118%5C%22%3Ecrater%20about%201.4%20metres%20deep%20and%2080%20metres%20wide%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%2085vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27161247%2FTrinity-test-obelisk.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27161247%2FTrinity-test-obelisk.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27161247%2FTrinity-test-obelisk-300x300.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27161247%2FTrinity-test-obelisk-150x150.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-665461%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAn%20obelisk%20marks%20the%20site%20of%20Ground%20Zero.%20Photo%3A%20Samat%20Jain%2FFlickr%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%202.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEntertainment%20from%20horror%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOppenheimer%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0is%20the%20latest%20film%20that%20explores%20the%20history%20of%20the%20atomic%20bomb.%20Other%20films%20go%20beyond%20this%20summer%E2%80%99s%20blockbuster%20to%20depict%20the%20full%20horror%20of%20what%20Oppenheimer%20created.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJon%20Else%E2%80%99s%201981%20documentary%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1119%2F1.13083%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Day%20After%20Trinity%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20shows%20the%20real%20history%20behind%20Nolan%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3EOppenheimer%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%201983%20made-for-TV%20movie%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2020%2Ffilm%2Freviews%2Ftelevision-event-review-the-day-after-1234831819%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Day%20After%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20dared%20to%20show%20the%20uncomfortable%20images%20of%20nuclear%20Armageddon%20to%20American%20audiences.%20And%20Mick%20Jackson%E2%80%99s%201984%20British%20television%20show%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%