n-123072701040_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Ffinance-ministry-cautions-five-psbs-on-the-risk-of-credit-concentration-123072701040_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Ffinance-ministry-cautions-five-psbs-on-the-risk-of-credit-concentration-123072701040_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ousted%20president's%20party%20HQ%20set%20ablaze%20in%20Niger%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690479884000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F16FCB%2Fproduction%2F_130555149_p0g3c3yz.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-66332360%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Supporters%20of%20a%20coup%20take%20to%20the%20streets%2C%20with%20looting%20and%20demonstrations%20in%20the%20capital%20Niamey.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fav%2Fworld-africa-66332360%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22MPs%20Raise%20Concerns%20Over%20OTT%20Content%20Regulation%20as%20RS%20Passes%20Cinematograph%20Amendment%20Bill%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F06125855%2Fcinema-2093264_1920.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKolkata%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20As%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20on%20Thursday%20(July%2027)%20passed%20the%20Cinematograph%20Amendment%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20some%20members%20demanded%20that%20regulations%20be%20brought%20in%20for%20content%20on%20over-the-top%20(OTT)%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20amends%20the%20Cinematograph%20Act%2C%201952%20and%20aims%20to%20tackle%20piracy%20by%20making%20it%20an%20offence%20that%20may%20be%20punishable%20with%20a%20fine%20or%20imprisonment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Cinematograph%20Act%2C%201952%20constitutes%20the%20Board%20of%20Film%20Certification%20(CBFC)%20for%20certifying%20films%20for%20exhibition%2C%20the%20amendment%20adds%20certain%20additional%20categories%20based%20on%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20earlier%20Act%2C%20a%20film%20was%20certified%20without%20restriction%20under%20%E2%80%98U%E2%80%99%20category%2C%20but%20subject%20to%20guidance%20of%20parents%20or%20guardians%20for%20children%20below%2012%20years%20of%20age%20under%20%E2%80%98UA%E2%80%99%20category%2C%20or%20only%20for%20adults%20under%20%E2%80%98A%E2%80%99%2C%20or%20only%20to%20members%20of%20any%20profession%20or%20class%20of%20persons%20under%20%E2%80%98S%E2%80%99%20category.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20an%20analysis%20by%20PRS%20Legislative%20Research%2C%20the%20Bill%20substitutes%20the%20%E2%80%98UA%E2%80%99%20category%20with%20the%20following%20three%20categories%20to%20also%20indicate%20age-appropriateness%3A%20(i)%20UA%207%2B%3B%20(ii)%20UA%2013%2B%3B%20or%20(iii)%20UA%2016%2B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20age%20endorsement%20will%20make%20it%20subject%20to%20guidance%20of%20parents%20or%20guardians%2C%20and%20will%20not%20be%20enforceable%20by%20any%20other%20persons%20other%20than%20parents%20or%20guardians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20stop%20piracy%2C%20the%20Bill%20prohibits%20carrying%20out%20or%20abetting%3A%20(i)%20the%20unauthorised%20recording%20and%20(ii)%20unauthorised%20exhibition%20of%20films.%C2%A0%20Attempting%20an%20unauthorised%20recording%20will%20also%20be%20an%20offence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20offences%20are%20punishable%20with%20imprisonment%20between%20three%20months%20and%20three%20years%2C%20and%20a%20fine%20between%20Rs%203%20lakh%20and%205%25%20of%20the%20audited%20gross%20production%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20the%20certificate%20issued%20by%20the%20CBFC%20was%20for%20ten%20years%2C%20but%20with%20the%20new%20amendment%2C%20certificates%20will%20be%20perpetually%20valid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20also%20removes%20the%20power%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20examine%20and%20make%20orders%20in%20relation%20to%20films%20that%20have%20been%20certified%20or%20are%20pending%20certification.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20proposed%20amendments%20would%20make%20the%20certification%20process%20more%20effective%2C%20in%20tune%20with%20the%20present%20times%2C%20and%20comprehensively%20curb%20the%20menace%20of%20film%20piracy%2C%20and%20thus%20help%20in%20faster%20growth%20of%20the%20film%20industry%20and%20boost%20job%20creation%20in%20the%20sector%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Bill%20states%20in%20its%20statement%20of%20objects%20and%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMinister%20for%20information%20and%20broadcasting%20Anurag%20Thakur%20called%20the%20Bill%20%E2%80%9Crevolutionary%E2%80%9D%20and%20blamed%20the%20opposition%20for%20walking%20out%20of%20the%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERegulation%20of%20content%20on%20OTT%20platforms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20debate%20on%20this%20issue%20saw%20several%20speakers%20including%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20MPs%20Radha%20Mohan%20Das%2C%20Dr%20Sonal%20Mansingh%2C%20Pavitra%20Margherita%2C%20Dhananjay%20Bhimrao%20Mahadik%2C%20Kavita%20Patidar%2C%20Biplab%20Kumar%20Deb%2C%20Ajay%20Pratap%20Singh%2C%20GVL%20Narasimha%20Rao%2C%20Bhubaneswar%20Kalita.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20MPs%20like%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%E2%80%99s%20Prashanta%20Nanda%20and%20AIADMK%E2%80%99s%20M.%20Thambi%20Durai%20also%20spoke%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20supporting%20the%20Bill%2C%20the%20members%20raised%20several%20concerns%2C%20including%20explicit%20content%20on%20OTT%20platforms%20and%20the%20need%20for%20regulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENanda%20raised%20concerns%20over%20that%20the%20content%20on%20OTT%20platforms%20that%20show%20rape%2C%20bad%20language%2C%20and%20violence%2C%20explicitly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBJP%E2%80%99s%20G.V.L.%20Narasimha%20Rao%20said%20that%20while%20OTT%20platforms%20provide%20the%20opportunity%20to%20watch%20films%20in%20multiple%20languages%2C%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20examine%20the%20regulations%20that%20apply%20to%20OTT%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20there%20are%20no%20such%20regulations%2C%20I%20would%20like%20to%20know%20why%20the%20Cable%20and%20Television%20Act%2C%20which%20controls%20content%20on%20television%2C%20does%20not%20apply%20to%20OTT%20content%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20if%20an%20uncensored%20film%20is%20put%20on%20OTT%3F%20If%20you%20are%20not%20able%20to%20control%20OTT%2C%20how%20are%20you%20able%20to%20restrict%20censored%20content%20being%20shown%20as%20a%20part%20of%20the%20OTT%20film%20industry%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20there%20is%20no%20regulation%20in%20place%2C%20can%20we%20have%20a%20dialogue%20with%20the%20OTT%20industry%20to%20have%20self%20regulation%20on%20OTT%20content%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThakur%20said%20that%20while%20several%20members%20had%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20OTT%20content%2C%20a%20meeting%20on%20this%20matter%20was%20held%20last%20week%20where%20issues%2C%20including%20self-regulation%2C%20were%20discussed%20with%20the%20OTT%20players.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20told%20them%20in%20the%20meeting%20seven%20days%20ago%20that%20self-regulation%20means%20that%20the%20responsibility%20lies%20with%20you.%20If%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20do%20something%20about%20this%2C%20we%20will%20be%20forced%20to%20use%20other%20means.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20to%20give%20them%20space%20for%20creativity.%20It%20is%20a%20new%20platform%20and%20it%20might%20take%20some%20time.%20When%20they%20give%20their%20next%20report%2C%20we%20will%20also%20raise%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20MPs%20in%20the%20next%20meeting.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Findia%2Fworried-about-obscenity-india-asks-streamers-content-checks-2023-07-14%2F%5C%22%3EReuters%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20in%20a%20meeting%20held%20between%20the%20information%20and%20broadcasting%20ministry%20and%20streaming%20platforms%2C%20the%20government%20requested%20that%20their%20content%20be%20reviewed%20for%20violence%20and%20obscenity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20reportedly%20asked%20the%20streaming%20industry%20to%20consider%20an%20independent%20panel%20to%20review%20content%20so%20that%20unsuitable%20material%20could%20be%20taken%20out%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20Bill%20was%20supported%20by%20BJP%20MPs%20who%20were%20present%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20as%20well%20as%20NDA%20allies%2C%20some%20members%20also%20raised%20concerns%20that%20the%20new%20age-based%20categories%20may%20not%20be%20feasible.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMPs%20like%20Nanda%2C%20Thambi%20Durai%20and%20YSRCP%E2%80%99s%20S.%20Niranjan%20Reddy%20said%20that%20the%20age%20classification%20in%20the%20new%20Bill%20may%20not%20work%20out%20practically.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20won%E2%80%99t%20work%20out%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Thambi%20Durai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Thakur%20said%20in%20his%20closing%20statement%20that%20the%20age-based%20categories%20are%20self%20regulatory%20by%20parents%20and%20guardians%20and%20lays%20the%20responsibility%20on%20the%20society%20to%20decide%20whether%20the%20content%20is%20suitable%20for%20viewing%20for%20a%20certain%20age%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690479375000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F06125855%2Fcinema-2093264_1920.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmps-raise-concerns-over-ott-content-regulation-as-rs-passes-cinematograph-amendment-bill%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Bill%20amends%20the%20Cinematograph%20Act%2C%201952%20and%20aims%20to%20tackle%20piracy%20by%20making%20it%20an%20offence%20tha